tal parts move more smoothly it works more as a cleaner and grease cutter than a lubricant.";i:42;s:33:"The price of WD-40 is reasonable.";i:43;s:24:"But it is not permanent.";i:44;s:65:"You have to lubricate squeaky door hinges often if you use WD-40.";i:45;s:43:"Silicone Spray Lubricant Uses and Benefits.";i:46;s:61:"You can use silicone spray on the car doors garage doors etc.";i:47;s:64:"It is one of the best lubricants for door locks and door hinges.";i:48;s:34:"It lessens the squeaky door sound.";i:49;s:163:"About Press Copyright Contact us Creators Advertise Developers Terms Privacy Policy Safety How YouTube works Test new features Press Copyright Contact us Creators.";i:50;s:70:"The first big no-no is using WD-40 to lubricate the garage door parts.";i:51;s:101:"Instead the garage door pros recommend using a lithium spray lubricant or a silicone spray lubricant.";i:52;s:75:"Instead of lubricating a garage door track what you need to do is clean it.";i:53;s:25:"Click to see full answer.";i:54;s:80:"You cant just use any lubricant on your garage door without causing more damage.";i:55;s:73:"Many people try using WD-40 on their garage door which is a huge mistake.";i:56;s:57:"This tends to cause rusting rather than true lubrication.";i:57;s:80:"The best lubricant for garage doors is a silicone spray or white lithium grease.";i:58;s:46:"These greases work to truly lubricate all the.";i:59;s:121:"The mineral spirits in WD-40 evaporate within a week of the initial application leaving only a thin layer of mineral oil.";i:60;s:140:"Mineral oil alone cannot lubricate the high-stress parts of a door effectively nor can it survive the heat of summer or the chill of winter.";i:61;s:160:"It may be tempting to try WD-40 or some other product hanging around your toolshed but WD-40 is not a garage door lubricant and may even do more harm than good.";i:62;s:129:"Instead choose between silicone and lithium garage door lube in Phoenix AZ and get your doors operation working a little quieter.";i:63;s:125:"Anyone who has any automotive knowledge will tell you that PB Blaster is roughly 1000x better than WD-40 for loosening bolts.";i:64;s:58:"PB Blaster has corrosive properties that eat through rust.";i:65;s:34:"WD-40 is really only for cleaning.";i:66;s:119:"It is not a lubricant in fact after about 2 days it has a reverse effect when you try to use it to lubricate something.";i:67;s:124:"Blaster Garage Door Lubricant is a silicone-based lubricant that leaves a tack-free film that wont accumulate dust and dirt.";i:68;s:88:"In some instances its extreme pressure agents make it a suitable replacement for grease.";i:69;s:78:"It effectively helps stop squeaks associated with garage doors and mechanisms.";i:70;s:26:"Wont Accumulate Dust Dirt.";}}